11 years ago today the sun stopped shining nearly as brightly as it once did. My mom always told me to choose a career that I’d do for free. Cause if ya love it that much, it’ll never feel like work. That’s exactly what I did. 
She doled out love & kindness like it was candy. She owned chocolate stores for many years. She put her heart and soul into every homemade hand crafted chocolate, truffle, praline and freshly chocolate dipped strawberry that she made.
My mom & dad would wake up every morning to listen to me on the radio. They’d even call in quite frequently to chime in on whatever we were talking about. She’d come hang out with me at the radio station & I’d put her on the air. Mom, thank you for all the love that has forever filled all of our hearts. 
One of the last things she told me was “to continue to be KIND to everyone.” It’s my mom’s legacy, and that’s what I’ll continue to do. Now, go eat a delicious piece of chocolate & think of my sweet mom! ☀️🙌🏼❤️🙏🏼
